The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Bucknor felicitated 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The BCCI on Wednesday felicitated Steve Bucknor on his becoming the first umpire to officiate in 100 Tests. 

Former BCCI chief and CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya handed over a plaque to the West Indian shortly before the start of Day I action at the Eden. 

The Pakistan team also presented him a huge cake, which had ?Wishing You A Century? written on it. Pakistan captain Inzamam-ul Haq also helped Bucknor have a bite of the cake. 




